Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and simulations, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper deals with the concept of fairness, which is a topic in computational complexity theory, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
